<I>ubuntu pre-install ruby:

1. sudo apt-cache search ruby
 	*choose the version >= 1.9.3
2. sudo apt-get install ruby1.9.* 

<II>settting the octopress:

1. git clone git://github.com/imathis/octopress.git octopress
2. gem install bundler
3. bundle install
4. rake install 
5. create the github rep
6. rask setup_github_pages
7. rake generate
8. rake deploy
9. git add. 
   git commit
   git push


<III>new other pc:
1. git clone -b source git@github.com:username/username.github.com octopress
2. cd octopress
3. git clone git@github.com:username/username.github.com _deplot
4. cd _deploy
5. git pull origin master
6. cd ..
7. git pull origin source

<IV>wordpress posts import octopress
1. download tools : https://gist.github.com/chitsaou/1394128 
file: wordpressdotcom.rb move into the same of octopress's directory  
2. export the wordpress content to wordpress.xml in wordpress dashboard move into the same of octopress's directory
3. gem install hpricot
4. ruby -r "wordpressdotcom.rb" -e "Jekyll::WordpressDotCom.process"


<V> create new post
1. rake new_post["post name"]
2. open the "post name".markdown file ,edit it
3. rake generate
4. rake deploy
5. push file to github
	5.1 git add .
	5.2 git commit -m "commit message"\
	5.3 git push origin source
